+# Task: Premium dashboard redesign + IA fix (sandbox-only diff)
+
+## Environment (critical — read first)
+
+You are running in Replit sandbox. There is **no backend** here.
+The branch `main` already contains a dev-only auth bypass:
+- File `frontend/src/mocks/isBypassEnabled.ts` exports a flag
+- When `VITE_BYPASS_AUTH=true` in `frontend/.env`, the app auto-logs-in with a mock user, pre-seeds React Query with Ukrainian mock data for Dashboard, and shows a red "DEV MOCK MODE" strip at the top
+
+Before you start:
+```bash
+git pull origin main
+echo 'VITE_BYPASS_AUTH=true' > frontend/.env
+echo 'VITE_API_URL=' >> frontend/.env
+cd frontend && npm install && npm run dev
+```
+
+Open `/dashboard` — you must see the current state (KPIs, charts, mock data) BEFORE you touch anything. If you do not see it, stop and report; do not proceed blind.
+
+## What you must NOT do
+
+1. **Do NOT remove the red DEV MOCK MODE banner** — it is guarded by `isBypassEnabled` and disappears automatically in prod. Leave it alone.
+2. **Do NOT modify `frontend/src/mocks/*`** — those are the fuel for your screenshots. If the Dashboard needs a new field, extend the mock DTO type in `frontend/src/types/analytics.ts` AND extend `mockDashboardData.ts` so your redesign has data to render.
+3. **Do NOT touch backend code** (`src/AgroPlatform.Api/**`, `src/AgroPlatform.Application/**`, `src/AgroPlatform.Domain/**`, `src/AgroPlatform.Infrastructure/**`). This is frontend-only.
+4. **Do NOT change `frontend/package.json`** — any new dep must be justified and will block the PR. Reuse what is already there: Ant Design 5, Zustand, React Query, Leaflet, dayjs. No new chart library, no new animation library. Use CSS + existing antd + existing charts.
+5. **Do NOT rewrite routing, auth, stores, axios, i18n structure**. Scope is strictly dashboard + sidebar IA.
+6. **Do NOT break i18n**. Every new string goes into BOTH `frontend/src/i18n/uk.ts` AND `frontend/src/i18n/en.ts`. Ukrainian is primary.
+
+## Design direction
+
+The project already has a design system — read these first and follow them:
+- `frontend/src/styles/design-system.css` (tokens — navy "Command Center" + green brand)
+- `docs/design-system/README.md`
+- `.claude/skills/agroplatform-design/SKILL.md` ("21st.dev dark-premium aesthetic, radial accent glow, Geist typography, single living accent")
+
+Aesthetic keywords: **dark canvas, radial green accent glow, Geist font, premium SaaS finance dashboard feel, generous spacing, single living accent color**. Look at `docs/design-system/preview-v4.html` for reference.
+
+Current dashboard state (see attached screenshot): KPI hero row works, but:
+- KPI cards look flat — need subtle glass/gradient + delta indicator variety
+- Charts feel cramped and have no axis legends
+- Alerts panel is a wall of red — needs severity tiers and icons
+- Too much vertical whitespace between sections
+- No clear visual hierarchy for "what needs your attention RIGHT NOW"
+### Theme parity with Landing Page (MANDATORY)
+
+The dashboard MUST feel like it belongs to the same product as the landing page. Same palette, same typography, same accent glow, same card treatment, same button styles.
+
+Before touching any dashboard code, open and study:
+- `frontend/src/pages/Landing/LandingPage.tsx` and every CSS module / styled file it imports
+- Run the app and open `/landing` — screenshot the hero, a feature card, and the CTA button
+- Extract the exact tokens used there: background gradient, accent green (`--brand-500` / similar), card surface color, border style, shadow, radial glow position, font weights
+
+Apply the same visual language to the dashboard:
+- **Background**: same dark canvas + radial accent glow as the landing hero (positioned top-right or behind the KPI hero row, very subtle, ~8–12% opacity)
+- **Cards**: same surface color, same border (`1px solid rgba(...)` with the landing's stroke token), same corner radius, same inner top highlight
+- **Accent color**: ONE living green — identical hex / CSS variable on the landing. If the landing uses `--brand-500`, the dashboard must too. No second accent.
+- **Typography**: Geist (or whatever the landing uses — check and match). Same H1 weight/tracking for the page title «Головна панель» as landing's section headings. Tabular-nums for all numbers.
+- **Buttons**: primary CTA button on the dashboard header («Нова операція») must be visually identical to the landing's primary CTA — same fill, hover glow, border-radius, height, padding
+- **Chips / badges**: match landing's feature chips / eyebrow pills exactly
+- **Links and subtle text**: same muted color tokens
+
+Rule: **if a color, radius, shadow, or font-size exists on the landing, reuse its CSS variable — do not invent a new one**. If a dashboard element has no landing counterpart, derive the style from the closest landing element and add the resulting variable to `frontend/src/styles/design-system.css` so both pages share it.
+
+Include in the PR body a small table mapping dashboard elements to their landing equivalents (e.g. «KPI card = landing feature card», «Header CTA = landing hero primary button»).
+
+Sanity check before pushing: open `/landing` and `/dashboard` side-by-side in two browser windows and visually confirm they look like siblings, not cousins.
+## Required work — frontend-only, in this exact order
+
+### 1. Sidebar information architecture (business logic fix — do this first)
+
+**Current order is wrong for agri-ops.** The order must reflect the real daily workflow of a farm manager:
+
+**Correct order (top → bottom):**
+1. Головна панель (Dashboard)
+2. Поля (Fields)
+3. Склад і логістика (Warehouse group — Warehouses, Stock, Movements, Grain storage)
+4. **Виробництво** (Production group — Operations, Machinery, Fleet map) — **moved BELOW warehouse**
+5. Персонал (HR)
+6. Фінанси (Economics — Costs, P&L, Budget, Marginality)
+7. Аналітика (Analytics)
+8. Налаштування (Settings)
+
+Rationale: production operations (сівба, підживлення, обприскування) consume resources from the warehouse, so warehouse must be visible before production in the mental model. This matches how agronomists plan the day.
+
+File: most likely `frontend/src/components/Layout/AppLayout.tsx` or a sidebar menu config near it. Change only the group order; do not rename items, do not touch permissions/roles.
+
+### 2. Dashboard redesign — `frontend/src/pages/Dashboard.tsx` + its sub-components
+
+Keep the same 4 KPI tiles, same 3 widgets (alerts, chart, fields+operations lists), but elevate the execution:
+
+**KPI hero row (`KpiHeroRow`)** — 4 cards: area, season expenses, season revenue, season profit + margin.
+- Each card: title small uppercase, big number (Geist, tabular-nums), small delta chip with arrow (+5%, −3%) using green/amber tokens — not red for spend increases unless over budget
+- Subtle top-left radial glow in the accent color, matching the card's KPI type (area = neutral white, expenses = amber, revenue = green, profit = accent green with glow)
+- 1px border in `--surface-stroke`, slight inner highlight on top edge, no heavy drop-shadow
+
+**Period switcher (Day / Week / Month / Season)** — segmented control, top-right of the page header. Already exists — keep it, just polish: active state = filled accent, inactive = ghost. Persist choice in a local Zustand slice or `useState` (do not add a new store).
+
+**Alerts panel** — replace the two red strips with a proper "Потребує уваги" card:
+- Sectioned by severity: Critical (red), Warning (amber), Info (muted blue)
+- Each row: icon + title + count + chevron link to the relevant page
+- Max 5 rows visible, "Показати всі (N)" link below
+
+**Revenue vs Cost chart** — currently just a red line. Needs:
+- Two series: expenses (amber, area under) + revenue (green, line on top)
+- Month labels on X axis, formatted values on Y (₴ k / ₴ m auto-scale)
+- Hover tooltip showing both series and the profit delta
+- If project already uses Recharts/Chart.js — use it. If not, use whatever chart lib is already in `package.json`. **Do not add a new one.**
+
+**Fields status + Operations timeline** — two-column grid, equal height. Fields list: chip with crop icon/color, name, area, current stage. Operations timeline: vertical stepper, completed = filled green dot, pending = hollow, overdue = amber pulse.
+
+**Quick actions strip** — four buttons (create operation, add cost, record movement, log salary) — reduce visual weight, make them ghost buttons in a single row, not big tiles.
+
+### 3. Dashboard layout constraints
+
+- Max content width: 1440px, centered, 32px horizontal padding
+- Consistent 24px gap between sections, 16px inside cards
+- All cards use `--surface-bg-1` / `--surface-bg-2` from `design-system.css`
+- No inline hex colors anywhere — only CSS variables
+- All typography via Geist; tabular-nums for every number
+- Responsive: at ≤1024px the two-column grids collapse to single column; at ≤768px KPI row becomes 2×2
+
+### 4. Verification (mandatory before opening PR)
+
+```bash
+cd frontend
+npx tsc --noEmit                  # must be clean
+npm run build                     # must succeed
+npm test -- --run                 # all tests must pass
+grep -c "MOCK MODE" dist/assets/*.js   # should report only 1–2 (i18n strings), not mock code
+```
+
+Run the app with bypass and take 3 screenshots into `docs/screenshots/dashboard-v3/`:
+- `01-overview.png` — full dashboard at 1440px
+- `02-alerts.png` — alerts panel close-up
+- `03-chart.png` — revenue/cost chart with tooltip open
+
+Also take one screenshot at ≤768px showing the responsive layout: `04-mobile.png`.
+
+### 5. PR requirements
+
+- Branch name: `feat/dashboard-premium-v3`
+- Commit message: `feat(dashboard): premium redesign v3 + sidebar IA fix (production below warehouse)`
+- PR title: same as commit
+- PR body must include:
+  - Before / after screenshots
+  - List of every file touched (file count budget: ≤ 20 files)
+  - Explicit statement: "No backend changes, no package.json changes, no mock code changes, no auth changes"
+  - Note about the sidebar reorder being an IA business-logic fix
+- Do NOT merge. Leave open for human review.
+
+## If something blocks you
+
+- If a required design token is missing, add it to `design-system.css` (do not inline).
+- If you need a new DTO field for the redesign, add it to `frontend/src/types/analytics.ts` AND supply a value in `frontend/src/mocks/mockDashboardData.ts` in the same commit.
+- If `tsc` fails, fix before committing. Never `--skip-lib-check` around real errors.
+- If the chart you want is not possible with the existing lib, use a simpler visual (sparkline + numbers) — do not add a new library.
+
+## Done =
+
+All of: IA fix applied, dashboard redesigned to premium standard, 4 screenshots attached, all verification commands green, PR open and not merged, commit count small (1–3 commits max), zero changes outside the allowed scope.
